This paper describes a computer model of the evolution of culture using neural network-based agents. This suggests that the paper is likely to fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or machine learning (cs.LG). The model also involves the imitation of neighbors' actions, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) or systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the effects of population size and density, which could fall under the category of computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE). Overall, the most likely categories are cs.AI and cs.SI, followed by cs.SY, cs.CE, and cs.LG.
